title._content: [Portrait of June Christy, Georgie Auld, and Red Rodney, Club Troubadour, New York, N.Y., ca. Sept. 1947] (LOC)

description._content: Gottlieb, William P., 1917-, photographer. [Portrait of June Christy, Georgie Auld, and Red Rodney, Club Troubadour, New York, N.Y., ca. Sept. 1947] 1 negative : b&w ; 2 1/4 x 2 1/4 in. Caption from Down Beat: If you can pull yourself away, that's Georgie Auld in the background. June Christy had the mike at the Troubadour when our good man Gottlieb was around. Notes: Gottlieb Collection Assignment No. 064 Reference print available in Music Division, Library of Congress. Purchase William P. Gottlieb Forms part of: William P. Gottlieb Collection (Library of Congress). In: "June, Georgie on the street," Down Beat, v. 14, no. 19 (Sept. 10, 1947), p. 3. Subjects: Christy, June, 1925- Auld, Georgie, 1919- Rodney, Red Jazz musicians--1940-1950. Women jazz musicians--1940-1950. Jazz singers--1940-1950. Saxophonists--1940-1950. Trumpet players--1940-1950. Club Troubadour Format: Portrait photographs--1940-1950. Group portraits--1940-1950. Film negatives--1940-1950.
